THE REVOLUTION IN THE SOUTH, 1778-1781
The final phase of the American Revolution occurred largely in the South, which the British thought would be a more receptive region for their troops. This map reveals the many, scattered military efforts of the British and the Americans in those years, none of them conclusive. It also shows the final chapter of the Revolution around the Chesapeake Bay and the James River. * What errors led the British to their surrender at Yorktown?
